title: For Sale:  Smith and Wesson Model 65-5 .357 Magnum "Lady Smith"
postcontent: For sale is my model 65-5 Smith & Wesson .357 magnum / .38 special "Lady Smith" (LS) 3" barrel. This gun is a great shooter. I recently took it for trade but it isn't really what I was looking for. I'm more of a rifle sort of guy, but this gun has been a treat to shoot. I have put about 200 rounds through it in the last month or so. Never had a failure to fire.It is a pre-lock smith and locks up tight with perfect timing in double/single action. These are 6 shot K-Frame guns. Comes with 150ish rounds of 38 special +P. Serial Number puts this gun right around February 1992 manufacture date.Lady Smith Features:- Single action target trigger- Brushed stainless finish- Nice original rosewood grips in a box in like new condition- 3" barrel- Fully shrouded ejector rod.This is a great chance to own a rare piece. The 3" smith is regarded as one of the most desirable carry revolvers. There were very few 3" model 65 Smiths ever made in the non-LS configuration. The LS version has the fully guarded ejector rod which is a great feature in a carry gun. Make me an offer.
